WEBVTT

00:08.453 --> 00:12.287
What I'm saying is, in this world
there's the visceral and the ineffable.

00:12.373 --> 00:16.001
- Nobody's totally un-effable.
- Ha! Virgins are.

00:16.093 --> 00:20.723
- But you're the opposite of un-effable.
- Ineffable. It doesn't mean what you think.

00:20.813 --> 00:24.931
- It means you can't describe it in words.
- Describe what? Like sex?

00:27.493 --> 00:29.563
You two have zero vocab skills.

00:29.653 --> 00:32.850
You're bitter
cos you're the designated driver.

00:32.933 --> 00:36.403
What's that even mean - "degsinated"?

00:36.893 --> 00:39.248
What the hell is that?

00:42.933 --> 00:46.926
Male, mid-30s, attachment sites
suggest he was well-muscled,

00:47.013 --> 00:49.732
probably manual labour,
not weight-training.

00:49.813 --> 00:51.644
OK. What killed him?

00:51.733 --> 00:56.204
The sternal ribs are subluxated
at both the spine and the sternum.

00:56.293 --> 00:58.966
Indicating that he was crushed?

00:59.053 --> 01:01.851
Not crushed. Pinned.

01:02.333 --> 01:06.645
Smothered,
perhaps in an industrial accident.

01:06.733 --> 01:09.566
This the guy Bones is checking out
to replace Zack?

01:09.653 --> 01:13.362
- Clark Edison, Special Agent Seeley Booth.
- Hey, what's up?

01:13.453 --> 01:17.492
Bones - that's funny. That's what
all my friends called me back in college.

01:17.573 --> 01:21.646
Yeah, I like him.
You got a minute? One minute?

01:21.733 --> 01:24.725
Oh, are you going to a crime scene?
Do you need me?

01:24.813 --> 01:27.202
I'll let you know.

01:27.293 --> 01:31.081
- Did I get it right?
- Construction worker foundation collapse.

01:31.173 --> 01:36.042
- But I'm not impressing her.
- I'm still not certain what she thinks of me.

01:38.613 --> 01:40.843
- Why am I here?
- You used to like field work.

01:40.933 --> 01:45.449
- No car fires, no tanker trucks full of acid...
- You were insistent.

01:45.533 --> 01:50.971
- Don't tell me I'm out here for a simple...
- Now I can't get you out of your lab coat.

01:51.053 --> 01:53.647
With Zack gone,
I'm needed at the Jeffersonian.

01:53.733 --> 01:58.488
That kid seemed pretty good
with the sublixicated sternicalum... thing.

01:58.573 --> 02:01.565
- You used to correct me.
- Why am I here, Booth?

02:02.013 --> 02:06.484
Foster, get a backboard.
We got one we gotta stabilise.

02:07.133 --> 02:08.964
<i>- </i> Whoa...
- Mm-hm.

02:09.053 --> 02:13.251
So, it's been three months
since Zack shipped off to Iraq?

02:13.333 --> 02:17.406
- Uh-huh.
- How hard could it be to replace him?

02:18.053 --> 02:20.044
Male, Caucasian...

02:20.133 --> 02:22.693
I'm just saying -
you in the lab, me in the field...

02:22.773 --> 02:25.571
We are not working
at our full symbiotic potential.

02:25.653 --> 02:30.966
Late teens, early 20s,
completely devoid of flesh or odour.

02:31.053 --> 02:34.807
It seems like maybe
you don't wanna work with me any more.

02:34.893 --> 02:38.203
- I work with you.
- You know what I mean, Bones.

02:38.293 --> 02:43.731
- How did this skull get here?
- Ask our eyewitness. Come on.

02:43.813 --> 02:46.088
Let's go, buddy.

02:46.173 --> 02:49.324
- I'm not high.
- Neither am I. Why is he telling me that?

02:49.413 --> 02:52.211
The car reeked of dope.
Tell her what happened.

02:52.293 --> 02:57.048
I was driving behind a dump truck and...
that came flying off the back.

02:57.133 --> 03:00.091
- You think the skeleton is still in the truck?
- No.

03:00.173 --> 03:04.052
- Why?
- It didn't come flying out, it came flying off.

03:04.133 --> 03:06.488
- It bounced.
- Oh, bouncing skull.

03:06.573 --> 03:10.725
Perhaps you were under the influence
of tetrahydrocannabinol.

03:10.813 --> 03:12.212
- What?
- Weed.

03:12.293 --> 03:16.650
I wasn't high. I'm the designated driver.
You can piss-test me if you want.

03:16.733 --> 03:19.042
It's possible.

03:19.133 --> 03:21.727
If the truck were travelling
at a certain speed,

03:21.813 --> 03:27.843
a wind vortex or sheer could occur
capable of flinging the skull like...

03:27.933 --> 03:29.810
What?

03:30.373 --> 03:33.763
- What, Booth?
- Bones.

03:35.053 --> 03:38.932
Why would anyone
throw a skull off an overpass?

03:40.333 --> 03:44.167
So your husband signed his name
to the marriage licence with an X.

03:44.253 --> 03:45.368
Yeah.

03:45.453 --> 03:48.206
So you married a guy
without knowing his name.

03:48.293 --> 03:51.251
It was Fiji. OK?
I was on vacation.

03:51.333 --> 03:56.088
I'm... I'm not being judgmental,
I'm just trying to ascertain the facts.

03:56.173 --> 03:59.848
Did you consummate the marriage?

03:59.933 --> 04:04.449
Full moon, tropics... Yeah,
there was definite consummation activity.

04:04.533 --> 04:09.129
- We already looked into annulment.
- It requires consent from both parties.

04:09.213 --> 04:15.243
Which is why we need a private investigator -
to find the "husband" so we can get married.

04:15.333 --> 04:20.123
I'll need any description you can provide
of your husband - details, dates, photographs,

04:20.213 --> 04:22.681
uh... who else was there.

04:22.773 --> 04:26.163
Tall. Yes.

04:26.253 --> 04:28.244
Muscular.

04:29.173 --> 04:31.926
Black.
That's all I've got.

04:32.013 --> 04:34.402
You know what?
I think his name had a B in it.

04:34.493 --> 04:39.772
Actually, it could've been a K.
You know what? I could make you a sketch.

04:43.533 --> 04:44.522
Well?

04:44.613 --> 04:48.401
Scoring patterns on the forehead,
cheekbones, around the nose.

04:48.493 --> 04:51.246
- I meant Clark Edison.
- Who's Clark Edison?

04:51.333 --> 04:56.487
The brilliant forensic anthropologist who'd
bite off his own arm to be your assistant.

04:56.573 --> 04:59.531
I haven't decided yet.
Is that a problem?

04:59.613 --> 05:03.686
- No. I want you to be certain of your choice.
- Thank you.

05:03.773 --> 05:07.163
It's just that you've turned down
17 applicants already.

05:07.253 --> 05:10.643
It's a rarefied discipline.
There aren't many more candidates.

05:10.733 --> 05:13.566
I'll cover the lab work
until I find the right person.

05:13.653 --> 05:16.451
This is good.
The first time you've called in weeks.

05:16.533 --> 05:18.967
- There's scoring on the skull.
- <i>Scoring?</i>

05:19.053 --> 05:21.886
- Yes. Scrapes.
- Yeah, I know what "scoring" means.

05:21.973 --> 05:26.967
The scraping is uniform in spacing, but not
in depth, which suggests an ungual pattern.

05:27.053 --> 05:32.923
- What's an "uncle" pattern?
- No, ungual. G... Ungual.

05:33.013 --> 05:36.210
How do I say this
in a way that makes sense to Booth?

05:36.293 --> 05:39.729
- Something chewed on the skull.
- Oh. Like a bear or a dog.

05:39.813 --> 05:42.043
Human, Booth.
Dr Brennan is saying human.

05:42.133 --> 05:47.207
In the vernacular, our victim's face
was chewed off by a cannibal.

05:50.613 --> 05:51.602
OK.

